### King James Version: Exodus Chapter 27

<span id="001">1</span> And thou shalt make an
[altar](../ebd/ebd018.htm#006) of [shittim](../ebd/ebd339.htm#009.md)
[wood](../ebd/ebd383.htm#003.md), five cubits long, and five cubits broad;
the [altar](../ebd/ebd018.htm#006.md) shall be foursquare: and the height
thereof shall be three cubits.  

<span id="002">2</span> And thou shalt make the horns of it upon the
four corners thereof: his horns shall be of the same: and thou shalt
overlay it with [brass](../ebd/ebd064.htm#003.md).  

<span id="003">3</span> And thou shalt make his pans to receive his
[ashes](../ebd/ebd034.htm#000.md), and his shovels, and his basons, and his
fleshhooks, and his firepans: all the vessels thereof thou shalt make of
[brass](../ebd/ebd064.htm#003.md).  

<span id="004">4</span> And thou shalt make for it a
[grate](../ebd/ebd154.htm#007.md) of network of
[brass](../ebd/ebd064.htm#003.md); and upon the
[net](../ebd/ebd271.htm#002.md) shalt thou make four brasen rings in the
four corners thereof.  

<span id="005">5</span> And thou shalt put it under the compass of the
[altar](../ebd/ebd018.htm#006.md) beneath, that the
[net](../ebd/ebd271.htm#002.md) may be even to the midst of the
[altar](../ebd/ebd018.htm#006.md).  

<span id="006">6</span> And thou shalt make staves for the
[altar](../ebd/ebd018.htm#006.md), staves of
[shittim](../ebd/ebd339.htm#009) [wood](../ebd/ebd383.htm#003.md), and
overlay them with [brass](../ebd/ebd064.htm#003.md).  

<span id="007">7</span> And the staves shall be put into the rings, and
the staves shall be upon the two sides of the
[altar](../ebd/ebd018.htm#006.md), to bear it.  

<span id="008">8</span> Hollow with boards shalt thou make it: as it was
shewed thee in the [mount](../ebd/ebd260.htm#007.md), so shall they make
it.  

<span id="009">9</span> And thou shalt make the court of the
[tabernacle](../ebd/ebd356.htm#003.md): for the south side southward there
shall be hangings for the court of fine twined
[linen](../ebd/ebd229.htm#008.md) of an hundred cubits long for one side:  

<span id="010">10</span> And the twenty pillars thereof and their twenty
sockets shall be of [brass](../ebd/ebd064.htm#003.md); the hooks of the
pillars and their [fillets](../ebd/ebd133.htm#002.md) shall be of
[silver](../ebd/ebd344.htm#000.md).  

<span id="011">11</span> And likewise for the north side in length there
shall be hangings of an hundred cubits long, and his twenty pillars and
their twenty sockets of [brass](../ebd/ebd064.htm#003.md); the hooks of the
pillars and their [fillets](../ebd/ebd133.htm#002.md) of
[silver](../ebd/ebd344.htm#000.md).  

<span id="012">12</span> And for the breadth of the court on the west
side shall be hangings of fifty cubits: their pillars ten, and their
sockets ten.  

<span id="013">13</span> And the breadth of the court on the
[east](../ebd/ebd111.htm#000.md) side eastward shall be fifty cubits.  

<span id="014">14</span> The hangings of one side of the
[gate](../ebd/ebd143.htm#008.md) shall be fifteen cubits: their pillars
three, and their sockets three.  

<span id="015">15</span> And on the other side shall be hangings fifteen
cubits: their pillars three, and their sockets three.  

<span id="016">16</span> And for the [gate](../ebd/ebd143.htm#008.md) of
the court shall be an [hanging](../ebd/ebd163.htm#001.md) of twenty cubits,
of [blue](../ebd/ebd061.htm#003.md), and purple, and
[scarlet](../ebd/ebd323.htm#005.md), and fine twined
[linen](../ebd/ebd229.htm#008.md), wrought with needlework: and their
pillars shall be four, and their sockets four.  

<span id="017">17</span> All the pillars round about the court shall be
filleted with [silver](../ebd/ebd344.htm#000.md); their hooks shall be of
[silver](../ebd/ebd344.htm#000.md), and their sockets of
[brass](../ebd/ebd064.htm#003.md).  

<span id="018">18</span> The length of the court shall be an hundred
cubits, and the breadth fifty every where, and the height five cubits of
fine twined [linen](../ebd/ebd229.htm#008.md), and their sockets of
[brass](../ebd/ebd064.htm#003.md).  

<span id="019">19</span> All the vessels of the
[tabernacle](../ebd/ebd356.htm#003.md) in all the service thereof, and all
the pins thereof, and all the pins of the court, shall be of
[brass](../ebd/ebd064.htm#003.md).  

<span id="020">20</span> And thou shalt command the children of
[Israel](../ebd/ebd191.htm#000.md), that they bring thee pure oil
[olive](../ebd/ebd277.htm#009.md) beaten for the light, to cause the
[lamp](../ebd/ebd223.htm#007.md) to burn always.  

<span id="021">21</span> In the [tabernacle](../ebd/ebd356.htm#003.md) of
the [congregation](../ebd/ebd088.htm#004.md) without the vail, which is
before the [testimony](../ebd/ebd362.htm#008.md),
[Aaron](../ebd/ebd000.htm#001.md) and his sons shall order it from evening
to morning before the LORD: it shall be a statute for ever unto their
generations on the behalf of the children of
[Israel](../ebd/ebd191.htm#000.md).  

